==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Graphoscope
<hw>Graph"o*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>gra`fein</grk> to write + <ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>An optical instrument for magnifying engravings, photographs, etc.,
usually having one large lens and two smaller ones.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An optical device for showing (or photographing) an
image when projected upon the atmosphere as a screen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Graphotype</ent>⟦br⟧
